---
import ContentLayout from '@layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { hbLogos, hbRestrictLogos, colors, typography } from 'apps/data/brand-guideline';
---

<ContentLayout>
  <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">Brand Assets and Guidelines</h1>
  <p class="mb-6 text-xl tracking-normal font-light">
    Documentation to ensure Hummingbird's name, logo, & other brand assets’ consistency and integrity.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-12 tracking-normal">
    The Hummingbird brand is a core asset and a symbol of our commitment to quality, performance, and the open-source
    community. This document provides clear guidelines for the use of the Hummingbird name, logo, and other brand
    assets, ensuring consistency and maintaining the integrity of our identity.
  </p>

  <!-- name -->
  <h3 class="mb-3.5 text-2xl font-semibold">Name</h3>
  <p class="mb-6 tracking-normal">
    The project's official name is "Hummingbird." This name should be used in all public-facing communications.
  </p>
  <div class="mb-14 flex items-center gap-6">
    <div class="card flex flex-col w-full h-[162px] rounded-2xl bg-default overflow-hidden">
      <div class="grow flex items-center justify-center bg-subtle">
        <h3 class="mb-0 text-default text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-normal">Hummingbird</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="px-4 py-2">
        <p class="card-title mb-0 text-muted text-sm tracking-normal font-medium">Correct</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card flex flex-col w-full h-[162px] rounded-2xl bg-default overflow-hidden">
      <div class="grow flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-subtle">
        <h3 class="text-default text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-normal">HummingBird</h3>
        <h3 class="mb-0 text-default text-[28px] font-semibold tracking-normal">hummingbird</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="px-4 py-2">
        <p class="card-title mb-0 text-muted text-sm tracking-normal font-medium">Incorrect</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- logo & symbol -->
  <h3 class="mb-3.5 text-2xl font-semibold">Logo & Symbol</h3>
  <p class="mb-6 tracking-normal">
    The official Hummingbird logo is our most recognizable brand asset and a key indicator of authenticity. The logo may
    not be used in a way that implies an endorsement, partnership, or affiliation with your project or company without
    explicit written permission. The logo may not be used as the primary logo for your own product or service.
  </p>
  <div class="mb-14 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
    {
      hbLogos.map((item, i) => (
        <div
          class={`card relative flex items-center justify-center w-full h-49 rounded-2xl ${i === 2 || i === 5 ? 'bg-gray-950' : i == 1 || i === 4 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-default'} overflow-hidden`}
        >
          <img src={item.src} alt="logo" />
          <a
            href={item.src}
            download={`logo-${i + 1}.svg`}
            class="absolute top-5 right-5 btn btn-subtle-neutral btn-circle btn-sm"
          >
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path
                d="M9 11.9062C8.925 11.9062 8.85625 11.8938 8.79375 11.8687C8.73125 11.8438 8.66875 11.8 8.60625 11.7375L5.775 8.90625C5.6625 8.79375 5.60938 8.65937 5.61563 8.50312C5.62188 8.34687 5.68125 8.2125 5.79375 8.1C5.90625 7.9875 6.04062 7.93125 6.19687 7.93125C6.35312 7.93125 6.4875 7.9875 6.6 8.1L8.4375 9.95625V3.5625C8.4375 3.4 8.49062 3.26563 8.59687 3.15938C8.70312 3.05313 8.8375 3 9 3C9.1625 3 9.29688 3.05313 9.40313 3.15938C9.50938 3.26563 9.5625 3.4 9.5625 3.5625V9.95625L11.4188 8.1C11.5312 7.9875 11.6656 7.93125 11.8219 7.93125C11.9781 7.93125 12.1125 7.9875 12.225 8.1C12.3375 8.2125 12.3937 8.34687 12.3937 8.50312C12.3937 8.65937 12.3375 8.79375 12.225 8.90625L9.39375 11.7375C9.33125 11.8 9.26875 11.8438 9.20625 11.8687C9.14375 11.8938 9.075 11.9062 9 11.9062ZM4.125 15C3.825 15 3.5625 14.8875 3.3375 14.6625C3.1125 14.4375 3 14.175 3 13.875V11.7563C3 11.5938 3.05313 11.4594 3.15938 11.3531C3.26563 11.2469 3.4 11.1938 3.5625 11.1938C3.725 11.1938 3.85937 11.2469 3.96562 11.3531C4.07187 11.4594 4.125 11.5938 4.125 11.7563V13.875H13.875V11.7563C13.875 11.5938 13.9281 11.4594 14.0344 11.3531C14.1406 11.2469 14.275 11.1938 14.4375 11.1938C14.6 11.1938 14.7344 11.2469 14.8406 11.3531C14.9469 11.4594 15 11.5938 15 11.7563V13.875C15 14.175 14.8875 14.4375 14.6625 14.6625C14.4375 14.8875 14.175 15 13.875 15H4.125Z"
                fill="currentColor"
              />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </div>

  <!-- things to avoid -->
  <div class="swiper">
    <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
      <div class="max-w-180">
        <h6 class="mb-3.5 text-xl font-medium">Things to avoid</h6>
        <p class="mb-6 tracking-normal">
          The logo cannot imply endorsement or affiliation with your project or company without written permission. It
          also cannot serve as the primary logo for your product or service.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <button class="swiper-button-prev !relative !left-0 !mt-0 !btn !btn-subtle-neutral !btn-circle">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="!w-5">
            <path
              d="M11.2305 15.097L7.10547 10.972C7.03602 10.9026 6.98741 10.8331 6.95964 10.7637C6.93186 10.6942 6.91797 10.6178 6.91797 10.5345C6.91797 10.4512 6.93186 10.3748 6.95964 10.3053C6.98741 10.2359 7.03602 10.1664 7.10547 10.097L11.2513 5.95117C11.3763 5.82617 11.5256 5.76367 11.6992 5.76367C11.8728 5.76367 12.0221 5.82617 12.1471 5.95117C12.2721 6.07617 12.3312 6.22895 12.3242 6.40951C12.3173 6.59006 12.2513 6.74284 12.1263 6.86784L8.45964 10.5345L12.1471 14.222C12.2721 14.347 12.3346 14.4928 12.3346 14.6595C12.3346 14.8262 12.2721 14.972 12.1471 15.097C12.0221 15.222 11.8694 15.2845 11.6888 15.2845C11.5082 15.2845 11.3555 15.222 11.2305 15.097Z"
              fill="currentColor"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <button class="swiper-button-next !relative !right-0 !mt-0 !btn !btn-subtle-neutral !btn-circle">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="!w-5">
            <path
              d="M7.37692 15.0972C7.2658 14.9583 7.20678 14.8055 7.19983 14.6388C7.19289 14.4722 7.25192 14.3263 7.37692 14.2013L11.0436 10.5347L7.35608 6.84718C7.24497 6.73606 7.19289 6.58676 7.19983 6.39926C7.20678 6.21176 7.2658 6.06245 7.37692 5.95134C7.5158 5.81245 7.66511 5.74648 7.82483 5.75343C7.98455 5.76037 8.12691 5.82634 8.25191 5.95134L12.3977 10.0972C12.4672 10.1666 12.5158 10.2361 12.5436 10.3055C12.5714 10.375 12.5852 10.4513 12.5852 10.5347C12.5852 10.618 12.5714 10.6944 12.5436 10.7638C12.5158 10.8333 12.4672 10.9027 12.3977 10.9722L8.27275 15.0972C8.14775 15.2222 8.00191 15.2812 7.83525 15.2743C7.66858 15.2673 7.5158 15.2083 7.37692 15.0972Z"
              fill="currentColor"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-14 swiper-wrapper">
      {
        hbRestrictLogos.map((item) => (
          <div class="swiper-slide">
            <div class="card flex flex-col w-full h-55 rounded-2xl bg-default overflow-hidden">
              <div class="grow flex items-center justify-center bg-subtle">
                <img src={item.img.src} alt="logo" />
              </div>
              <div class="px-4 py-2">
                <p class="card-title mb-0 text-muted text-sm tracking-normal font-medium">{item.title}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- color -->
  <h3 class="mb-3.5 text-2xl font-semibold">Color</h3>
  <p class="mb-6 tracking-normal">
    Color is the base of MailBluster. It characterizes our brand and helps us to create consistent experiences across
    marketing and products. We use color in meaningful ways in all appearances of our brand. Please don’t edit, change,
    or add additional color to the palette.
  </p>
  <div class="mb-14 grid grid-cols-10 gap-4">
    {
      colors.map((c) => {
        return c.items ? (
          <div class={`flex flex-col gap-4 h-60 ${c.span}`}>
            {c.items.map((c, i) => (
              <div
                class={`card rounded-2xl p-6 flex flex-col justify-between h-full ${i === 0 ? 'text-black' : 'text-white'} ${c.bgColor}`}
              >
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-tight">{c.name}</h3>
                <p class="mb-0 mt-auto font-bold tracking-normal">{c.hex}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        ) : (
          <div
            class={`card rounded-2xl p-6 flex flex-col justify-between h-60 text-white ${c.span}`}
            style={`background-color: ${c.hex}`}
          >
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-tight">{c.name}</h3>
              <p class="font-medium tracking-normal">{c.role}</p>
            </div>
            <p class="mb-0 mt-auto font-bold tracking-normal">{c.hex}</p>
          </div>
        );
      })
    }
  </div>

  <!-- typography -->
  <h3 class="mb-3.5 text-2xl font-semibold">Typography</h3>
  <p class="mb-6 tracking-normal">
    We design to reduce the friction between people and their tools and ultimately achieve their goals. We’ve chosen a
    full font stack that transitions from friendly and warm in marketing to simple and focused on the product to
    accomplish this across our brand. We are here using the font Figtree for our typography.
  </p>
  <div class="mb-14 p-4 rounded-xl bg-subtle">
    <div class="mb-6 flex justify-between">
      <h1 class="text-[56px] text-primary font-semibold">Figtree</h1>
      <div class="">
        <p class="mb-1.5 text-sm text-right tracking-normal">Designer <b class="font-semibold">Erik Kennedy</b></p>
        <p class="text-sm text-right tracking-normal">
          Source <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Figtree" class="no-underline">Google Fonts</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-5 gap-2">
      {
        typography.map((item) => (
          <div class="card px-3.5 py-2 text-default flex-row gap-2 rounded-lg">
            <h1 class={`mb-0 text-[42px] ${item.class}`}>Aa</h1>
            <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium tracking-normal">
              <p class="mb-0">{item.label}</p>
              <p class="mb-0">{item.weight}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- fair use -->
  <h3 class="mb-3.5 text-2xl font-semibold">Fair use</h3>
  <p class="mb-4 tracking-normal">
    We encourage the community to create content about Hummingbird. The use of our name and logo in articles, tutorials,
    and public discussions is permitted, provided it adheres to these guidelines and does not imply official
    endorsement.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4 tracking-normal">
    Any use of the Hummingbird name or logo in a manner that could cause user confusion is not permitted.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4 tracking-normal">
    This includes naming a product or service in a way that emphasizes the Hummingbird brand, such as “Hummingbird
    Themes,” “Hummingbird Pro,” or “Hummingbird Templates,” as well as in domain names like hummingbird-dashboard.com.
    Instead, your own brand name must be the clear and primary identity of your project.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4 tracking-normal">
    Referencing Hummingbird as the underlying technology is highly encouraged. For instance, “Admin Dashboard built with
    Hummingbird” or “DesignKit - A UI Kit for Hummingbird” are both excellent examples of permitted use.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4 tracking-normal">
    By following these guidelines, you help us ensure that the Hummingbird brand remains a trusted and reliable mark of
    quality for developers everywhere. Thank you for your support.
  </p>

  <script>
    import Swiper from 'swiper/bundle';
    import 'swiper/css/bundle';

    const swiper = new Swiper('.swiper', {
      loop: true,
      slidesPerView: 3.5,
      spaceBetween: 16,
      navigation: {
        nextEl: '.swiper-button-next',
        prevEl: '.swiper-button-prev',
      },
    });
  </script>
</ContentLayout>
